headline: Trump’s Truck Tariffs Are Coming. Here’s Who Wins and Loses.
summary: Shares of heavy-duty truck maker  Paccar  rose early Friday after President Donald Trump announced new tariffs on foreign-made heavy-duty trucks on Thursday.  “In order to protect our Great Heavy Duty Truck Manufacturers from unfair outside competition, I will be imposing, as of October 1st, 2025, a 25% tariff on all Heavy (Big!) Trucks made in other parts of the World,” the president said on Truth Social.  “Therefore, our Great Large Truck Company Manufacturers, such as Peterbilt, Kenworth, Freightliner, Mack Trucks, and others will be protected.”

headline: The Winners and Losers From Trump’s 25% Truck Tariffs
summary: “Our Great Large Truck Company Manufacturers, such as Peterbilt, Kenworth, Freightliner, Mack Trucks, and others, will be protected from the onslaught of outside interruptions,” wrote President Trump Thursday evening when he announced a 25% tariff on heavy trucks.  In fact, a key target of the new tax appears to be one of the brands the president said he wants to protect: Freightliner, which is owned by Germany’s Daimler Trucks and assembles most of its vehicles in Mexico.  Shares in Volkswagen’s truck subsidiary Traton, which makes international trucks almost exclusively in Mexico, fell around the same.
